28/10/2003
ZAGREB, Croatia -- The leaders of the major opposition coalition in Croatia -- the Croatian Social Liberal Party's (HSLS) Drazen Budisa and the Democratic Centre's (DC) Mate Granic -- met with EU member state ambassadors on Monday (27 October). 
Talks focused on the political situation and the 23 November parliamentary elections. 
The HSLS-DC coalition leaders said they plan to talk with other opposition parties in hopes of expanding the coalition. 
Budisa predicts it will win at least 20 seats in the 151-member parliament. 
(HINA, BBC - 27/10/03)
